{{> header/header-block}}
<div class="section">
    <h1 class="mainH" id="aboutCont">About Me</h1>
    <p id="intro">Hello! My name is John, but I go by JJ. I am a fast learning web developer based in Sacramento, CA.
        I enjoy using new technology, cooking, and tinkering with computers & cars. Currently, I'm attending
        a full-stack coding bootcamp at UC Davis and creating lots of great web applications with a variety of
        widely used languages. Check out some of my projects below and get in
        contact if you would like to work with me, I am always looking to expand my network!
    </p>
</div>
<div class="section" id="projectsCont" data-aos="zoom-in">
    <h1 class="mainH">Projects</h1>
    <div class="glide">
        <div class="glide__track" data-glide-el="track">
            <ul class="glide__slides">
                <li class="glide__slide">
                    <div class="glideCard" id="TSNCard">
                        <h class="glideCardH">The Social Network</h>
                        <div class="projectBtns">
                            <a class="pbtn" href="https://github.com/Guhuyan/Project-2">Code</a>
                            <a class="pbtn" href="https://tranquil-wave-24974.herokuapp.com/">Demo</a>

                        </div>
                        <div class="projectDesc" id="TSNI">Node-Express application where users can create an
                            account/login, make posts which display on the dashboard, and chat in real time. I
                            worked on the live chat room, created sequelize models, pulled data from the
                            database for dynamic rendering, and converted the initial front end html into
                            handlebars templates.

                        </div>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="glide__slide">
                    <div class="glideCard" id="EDBCard">
                        <h class="glideCardH">Eat Da Burger</h>
                        <div class="projectBtns">
                            <a class="pbtn" href="https://github.com/jjmateer/Burger">Code</a>
                            <a class="pbtn" href="https://eat-da-burger22.herokuapp.com/">Demo</a>

                        </div>
                        <div class="projectDesc" id="EDBI">Node-express application which allows users to post
                            burgers and devour them. This app uses a mySQL database with an ORM to store
                            burgers and dynamically render them with handlebars.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="glide__slide">
                    <div class="glideCard" id="GSCard">
                        <h class="glideCardH">Giphy Search</h>
                        <div class="projectBtns">
                            <a class="pbtn" href="https://github.com/jjmateer/Giphy-Search">Code</a>
                            <a class="pbtn" href="https://jjmateer.github.io/Giphy-Search/">Demo</a>
                        </div>
                        <div class="projectDesc" id="GSI">Application which allows users to search for gifs and
                            play/stop them. This app uses jQuery to render a button with the user's search,
                            uses that term to search the Giphy API and renders the first 25 results to the page.

                        </div>
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="glide__arrows" data-glide-el="controls">
            <button id="glideControls" class="glide__arrow glide__arrow--left" data-glide-dir="<">
                LAST</button> <button id="glideControls" class="glide__arrow glide__arrow--right"
                data-glide-dir=">">NEXT
            </button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="section" id="contactCont" data-aos="zoom-in">
    <form id="contactForm" method="POST" action="send">
        <h1 class="mainH">Contact</h1>
        <span class="contactlabels">Name</span>
        <input required class="formInputs" placeholder="Ex: John Johnson" id="name" />
        <span class="contactlabels">Email</span>
        <input required class="formInputs" placeholder="Ex: name@email.com" id="email" />
        <span class="contactlabels">Message</span>
        <textarea required class="formInputs" placeholder="Enter message here..." id="message"></textarea>
        <button id="submitBtn" type="submit">Send</button>
    </form>
</div>